FBIS4-62274 "drsov093_d_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-093 Daily Report 12 May 1994 Regional Affairs Kuban Crime Crackdown Produces Results Kuban Crime Crackdown Produces Results PM1205141994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 12 May 94 First Edition p 8 PM1205141994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [Unattributed report: "Militia's `Catch'"] [Text] As ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA has already reported, kray administration head Nikolay Yegorov's decree "On Emergency Measures To Combat Crime," has come into force in the Kuban. In accordance with this decree mass surveillance and preventive and investigations measures were carried out in the course of four days; around 10,000 militia officers took part in these measures. The "catch" was fairly considerable and diverse. During the operation 344 crimes were detected, including 22 cases of premeditated murder, 16 cases of deliberate aggravated assault, 25 robberies and muggings, 140 cases of embezzlement of state and private property, and 12 thefts of firearms and munitions. Fifty illegally held weapons were seized and 14 stolen cars were restored to their lawful owners; money and valuables to the tune of 15 million rubles were seized from criminals. Eighty five criminals hiding from investigation and justice were found. The kray's hotels, stations, and markets were checked in a search for "casual workers."
